# eval-rubric.yml
# Used by: domain-ingest workflow (Phase 2)
# Purpose: Score candidate agent files from GitHub and VoltAgent catalog
#          before synthesizing them into dream-studio's agents/ and skills/domains/.
# When to use: Run this rubric against each candidate file BEFORE deciding
#              whether to bundle it as an agent or extract domain YAML only.
# Score = count of signals present (0-8). See thresholds block for cutoffs.

scoring_guidance:
  process:
    - Read the candidate file top to bottom once
    - For each signal in the signals block, check the how_to_score criteria
    - Mark each signal as present (1) or absent (0)
    - Sum the marks to get a total score (0-8)
    - Apply the threshold from the thresholds block
  notes:
    - Signals are binary  -  present or absent, no partial credit
    - When in doubt, mark absent  -  only mark present if the evidence is explicit
    - Score reflects dream-studio fitness, not general agent quality
    - A file scoring 8/8 on general polish but 2/8 here is still a reject

signals:
  - id: has_gotchas
    description: >
      Non-obvious failure modes, edge cases, or runtime traps are explicitly
      documented. These are things that will bite a developer who skips the file
      and tries to use the tool from memory alone.
    how_to_score: >
      Look for a "Gotchas", "Pitfalls", "Common errors", "Watch out", or
      "Known issues" section, or inline warnings prefixed with NOTE/WARNING/CAUTION.
      Generic disclaimers ("results may vary") do not count.
    example_pass: '"Gotcha: Claude resets tool_choice to auto after the first tool call  -  always re-set it per turn."'
    example_fail: '"This tool may not work in all environments."'

  - id: has_anti_patterns
    description: >
      Explicit what-not-to-do guidance with concrete examples of wrong usage.
      Covers patterns that appear reasonable but produce broken or unsafe output.
    how_to_score: >
      Look for sections titled "Anti-patterns", "Don't", "Avoid", "Bad example",
      or inline [x]/[x] markers with explanatory text. Must name the pattern and
      explain why it fails  -  listing it without explanation does not count.
    example_pass: '"Anti-pattern: passing the full conversation history to every tool call  -  causes context bloat and token waste."'
    example_fail: '"Avoid misuse of this API."'

  - id: has_specific_commands
    description: >
      Real, runnable CLI commands or tool invocations are shown, not conceptual
      descriptions of what a command does. Commands must be copy-pasteable.
    how_to_score: >
      Look for code blocks containing shell commands, API calls with real flags,
      or SDK snippets with actual method signatures. Pseudocode, placeholder-only
      examples ("run <your-command>"), and prose descriptions do not count.
    example_pass: '"gh pr create --title \"fix: auth token refresh\" --body \"Fixes #42\" --base main"'
    example_fail: '"Use the GitHub CLI to create a pull request with the appropriate title."'

  - id: has_version_specifics
    description: >
      Current, pinned tool versions or API version numbers are cited, not
      timeless prose that could apply to any version. Enables compatibility checks.
    how_to_score: >
      Look for explicit version numbers (e.g., "Node 20.x", "wrangler@3.78",
      "claude-3-7-sonnet-20250219"). Date-stamped changelogs also count.
      Phrases like "the latest version" or "modern Node" do not count.
    example_pass: '"Tested with wrangler@3.78.0 and @cloudflare/workers-types@4.20250409.0."'
    example_fail: '"Works with the latest version of Wrangler."'

  - id: battle_tested
    description: >
      The file originates from or is referenced in a production repository, not
      just a catalog, template gallery, or marketing page. Production origin
      signals real-world validation.
    how_to_score: >
      Check file provenance metadata (source_repo, origin_url, or ingest-log.yml
      entry). A GitHub repo with commits, issues, or release history counts.
      A VoltAgent catalog entry with no linked repo does not count unless it
      references a production deployment.
    example_pass: "source_repo: github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk  -  2,400 stars, active issues"
    example_fail: "source: VoltAgent catalog listing, no linked repository"

  - id: workflow_integrable
    description: >
      The agent produces verifiable, structured artifacts (files, database rows,
      structured JSON, PR URLs, test reports) that downstream steps can consume.
      Pure advisory output (summaries, recommendations) does not count.
    how_to_score: >
      Look for output schemas, artifact declarations, or examples showing a file
      path, URL, or structured payload produced by the agent. The output must
      be something a subsequent workflow step could programmatically verify.
    example_pass: '"Outputs: { pr_url: string, commit_sha: string, files_changed: number }"'
    example_fail: '"The agent will provide recommendations for improving your codebase."'

  - id: has_concrete_examples
    description: >
      Real input/output pairs are shown  -  not templates or placeholder text.
      Examples demonstrate the actual behavior on a specific, realistic scenario.
    how_to_score: >
      Look for before/after code, sample prompts with actual responses, or
      terminal transcripts showing real output. Placeholder text ("your input here",
      "<example>") and synthetic lorem-ipsum content do not count.
    example_pass: 'Input: "fix the auth bug" -> Output: PR #88 opened at github.com/org/repo/pull/88'
    example_fail: "Input: <your task description> -> Output: <agent response>"

  - id: maintained_recently
    description: >
      The file or its source repository was last updated within 90 days of the
      ingest date. Signals that the content reflects current tool behavior.
    how_to_score: >
      Check the file's last_updated field, git log date for the source repo,
      or the ingest-log.yml recorded_at timestamp. If no date is available,
      mark absent. "Recently updated" claims without a date do not count.
    example_pass: "last_updated: 2025-03-14  -  within 90 days of ingest date 2025-04-29"
    example_fail: "No date metadata present in file or source repository."

thresholds:
  bundle_as_agent:
    min_score: 5
    action: >
      Synthesize a full agent YAML under agents/ and wire it into the skill
      registry. This file is high-fidelity enough to drive automated behavior.
  domain_yaml_only:
    min_score: 4
    action: >
      Extract domain knowledge into skills/domains/ as reference YAML.
      Do not create an agent entry. Use for reference and scoring context only.
  reject:
    max_score: 3
    action: >
      Do not ingest. Log the candidate in ingest-log.yml with status: rejected
      and the score. Review again if the source file is updated.


